result.name: King's Dumpling

reviews.text: Food was not very good. The Xiao long bao was the best part of the meal. In addition cockroaches climbed into our table while we were eating. The staff just shrugged and moved us to a different table. Finished as fast as possible and left asap. Didn't have much of an appetite after anyway.

Enjoyed the food very much especially the dumplings which were great with a bit of soy sauce and vinegar as well as the pork knuckles even though they were a bit out of my comfort zone. Staff was very friendly as well

Stopped here for lunch and we didn't know Chinese. We may have gotten lucky but the staff were very accommodating. We ordered just a couple of dim sum and service was quick. One order came out wrong but with some pointing and shaking they were fast to fix it. Food was okay. This was in December so they had decorations out and some annoying thing playing the same carol the whole time we were there. The stars are given for the service we received which was probably the best we had in Hong Kong.

Hm... I hate to give 5 stars because I'm afraid this restaurant gets popular and busy, but can't find any reason giving less than 5. It is located in the middle of busy shop area I square. Environment was clean and easy to access. People were nice and gentle. Easy to order and served within a reasonable time.

We made choices mostly among taiwan style dishes, and all were admired by our companions. The manue offers various chines cuisines from different places, so you may try many options. And the prices were quite reasonable compared with others around the building.

The Dan Dan noodles really didn't taste that good, and dried out really quickly because the noodles absorbed all the water.  The minced meat rice (肉燥飯) was tasty but too oily.  The dumplings were alright but not remarkable.  Would probably not visit again.  Service is also quite slow.  We waited at least 5 minutes in the queue to pay because there was a problem with the only card machine they had.

result.name: 金牌小龍

reviews.text:
上網睇有好多選擇，去到好多都無。環境幾清靜，因為客人唔算多😅。味道...超級失望...
因為價錢睇落唔算貴，我地兩個人叫左好多野：
牛肉麵（$58）：有三塊牛𦟌，啲牛𦟌幾淋，麵有啲硬，湯底好一般...
元盅雞湯（$52）：網評推介菜式，味道好普通😑
蟹黃瑤柱扒西蘭花（$88）：無蟹黃味道
甜不辣（炸魚片）（$38）：完全無魚味，一團炸粉...啲汁味道有啲怪，唔似台灣甜不辣，超難食
金牌小籠包（$42）：正正常常，都有啲湯汁，上枱時唔太熱
雞絲粉皮（$38）：粉皮有啲硬，但味道ok
酥炸黃花魚（$62）：條魚有啲細，炸得都脆，但都好一般，配埋個千島醬唔太夾
爆汁牛肉餡餅（$18）：都幾爆汁，味道唔錯，可惜皮太厚
整體唔合格，無要求可以一試。

本來有時得閒都幾中意特登黎呢間食麵
(Isquare 店)但今日啲食物質素 服務態度 衛生 真係不知所謂

我叫左碗擔擔撈麵 黎到之後係一滴湯都冇 又乾 啲麵我係要用一舊舊黎形容 我叫左個呀叔過黎 同佢講啲麵唔得 佢話我地啲麵係咁架喎 有湯果啲係京川 我地呢啲係台式 我表示我食過幾次我知道啲麵應該會係點 (請自行比較餐牌中嘅麵同我叫嘅麵) 佢話我俾返啲湯你 我話我要取消 佢話啲麵冇問題 死都要同我拗 ok 我唔抝 咁佢拎到啲清湯黎 (相中碗麵上面嘅碗仔) 我咪加少少試下 點知難死到dlgh 我成碗冇食 40幾蚊當豪俾佢算

我仲認得呢個呀叔 之前金牌小龍仲係the one 果陣 佢拎左碗擔擔撈麵黎 果次啲湯多L到寫 我問佢呢個係咩黎 佢話係撈麵 之後又要同我抝 

之於衛生問題 自己可以睇相 圖中liu 鼻屎個呀姐係負責煮麵 仲會用手嗱啲蔥 花生碎落你碗麵 係我order前佢同埋其他同事包括黑衫果啲竟然係廚房到食嘢 佢地知唔知果個係open kitchen黎 係咪唔知咩叫7

經過今次之後我以後都唔會再去
位於尖沙咀國際大厦3樓，交通方便。菜牌有幾組套餐，不包加一，茶介。另一组則全包連豆漿一杯，價錢相差1O元左右。我嘗試叫两個不同套餐，聲稱推廣台灣食品，內有牛肉麫，炒飯及小食，除了牛肉麫加熱外，其他都是冷食，唯一賣點是一個男侍應熱誠值得稱讚外，其他並無吸引之處。

3층에 있는 식당인데 다양한 딤섬과 중국요리를 맛볼 수 있는 곳이에요. 
메뉴판에 사진이 있어서 메뉴판을 보고 주문표에 표시하면 되요. 
딤섬도 주문 즉시 만들어서 쩌주는 것 같아요
가격도 적당한 편인데 딤섬 한판에 40-50달러 정도에요. 
관광객 뿐만아니고 몰을 찾는 홍콩 거주인들도 많이 찾는 듯해요
주문한 샤오롱바오, 쇼마이, 완탕, 오이 모두 성공적이었어요
服務和衛生都十分惡劣,一坐落去枱面就有隻去就有隻蟑螂跑出來,簡直嚇死人。而且食物的味道很一般,不值得去試。

reviews.text: Isquare  Is a nice shopping mall it has really call art work in front of it. It's really busy has a lot of nice shops that are all open past 10:00 p.m. It's in a convenient location from the Subway. Has some good restaurants in it. And the movie theater

It's a modern and great design shopping center and close to my hotel. I went here for a lunch and found Mark & Spencer on the ground floor and shopped a bit here. Overall, it's a nice shopping center.
Good for shopping (M&S clothing and food hall, marketplace), kids-r-us and other kid brands, very good cinema, linked to TST MTR train station
Visited the EyeLounge.  Very nice location with breath taking views of the city! Good drinks and very nice restaurant and cuisine.
High end shopping mall in Kowloon. Big brands.
